===Etymology 1===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*peh₃-}}
Originally verb sense “drink heartily”, from {{inh|en|enm|bibben}}, either from {{der|en|la|bibō||I drink}} or of imitative origin. Noun sense (clothing) presumably either because worn while drinking, or because the clothing itself “drinks up” spills.<ref>{{R:Online Etymology Dictionary}}</ref>

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# An item of [[clothing]] for people (especially [[baby|babies]]) [[tie]]d around their [[neck]] to protect their clothes from getting dirty when eating.
# [[similar|Similar]] [[item]]s of [[clothing]] [[such as]] the [[Chinese]] [[dudou]] and [[Vietnamese]] [[yem]].
# {{lb|en|sports}} A rectangular piece of [[material]], carrying a [[bib number]], worn as [[identification]] by entrants in a race.
# {{lb|en|sports}} A colourful polyester or plastic vest worn over one's clothes, usually to mark one's team during group activities.
#: {{syn|en|pinny}}
# The upper part of an [[apron]] or [[overalls]].
# {{lb|en|cycling}} [[w:Cycling shorts|Shorts]] which are held up by [[suspenders]].
# A patch of colour around an animal's upper breast and throat.
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1950|author=Arthur Cleveland Bent|title=Life Histories of North American Wagtails, Shrikes, Vireos, and their Allies|passage=In summer the whole throat and breast are black, but in winter plumage the throat is white bounded by a horseshoe-shaped black '''bib'''.}}
